## Vercel Speed Insights Installation and Configuration

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the React + Vite project.

### Changes Made:

#### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` v2.0.0 to package.json dependencies
- Updated package-lock.json with the new package and its dependencies

#### 2. Modified Files
- **frontend/src/App.tsx**
  - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/react";`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the main App component, placed right after `<Analytics />`

### Implementation Details:

According to the official Vercel documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), for React/Vite applications:
- The `SpeedInsights` component should be imported from `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
- The component should be placed at the root level of the application to track all pages
- No additional configuration or environment variables are required for basic functionality

The implementation follows the same pattern already established in the project with the `@vercel/analytics` package, placing both Analytics and SpeedInsights components in the App.tsx file.

### Verification:

✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ TypeScript compilation passed
✅ All dependencies installed correctly
✅ SpeedInsights component properly integrated alongside existing Analytics

### Next Steps:

To see Speed Insights data:
1. Enable Speed Insights in your Vercel project dashboard
2. Deploy the application using `vercel deploy`
3. Visit your site to generate performance metrics
4. View the insights in your Vercel dashboard

No additional configuration is needed - Speed Insights will automatically start tracking performance metrics once deployed to Vercel.
